🔥 How to Smoke the Perfect Tenderloin 🔥
Bold bark. Juicy center. Wall-to-wall medium rare.

1️⃣ Season generously with your favorite BBQ rub
2️⃣ Smoke low & slow at 225°F until internal temp hits 120–125°F
3️⃣ Rest 30 minutes
4️⃣ Sear hard for a crust that crackles

This reverse-sear method guarantees flavor AND tenderness.
Perfect for family gatherings—or just flexin’ on a Tuesday. 🥩💪

🔥 How to Keep a Medium-Well Steak Tender 🔥
Most folks mess this up… but it’s fixable. The secret? Go thin and fatty. A thick filet mignon? That’s a one-way ticket to dry-town.
👉 Instead, grab a thin-cut ribeye or anything with good marbling. Cook it medium-well, rest it right—and it’ll still melt in your mouth.
🥩 Fat saves the day when moisture is lost. Remember: fat = flavor = forgiveness.

😊 The steak in this video was provided by @_diamond_h_ranch 

#steak #bbq #grilling

👉 5 Tips For Cooking a Better Steak 🥩 #bbq #grilling #meat

🔥 Tired of ruining your steaks? Here’s how to do it RIGHT.
Smoked steaks are next level—and this method makes it stupid simple:
	1.	Rub your steak with beef base as a binder and season generously with “Box Yo Mama” rub.
	2.	Set your smoker to 225°F (I used the @greenmountaingrills Ledge).
	3.	Smoke until it hits 130°F internally—about 90 minutes.
	4.	Let it rest for 20 minutes, then sear hot and fast.
	5.	Slice it up and enjoy that juicy perfection.

👉 I prefer medium rare, so I pull mine at 130–135°F. Want it more done? Keep it going a little longer.

#bbq #steak #grilling
